effect:
User [switches out]{mechanic:switches out}, and the trainer selects a replacement Pokémon from the party.  [Stat]{mechanic:stat} changes, [confusion]{mechanic:confusion}, and persistent move effects are passed along to the replacement Pokémon.

The following move effects are passed:

* [Aqua Ring]{move:aqua-ring}
* both the user's and target's effect of [Block]{move:block}, [Mean Look]{move:mean-look}, and [Spider Web]{move:spider-web}
* the curse effect of [Curse]{move:curse}
* [Embargo]{move:embargo}
* [Focus Energy]{move:focus-energy} or an activated [Lansat Berry]{item:lansat-berry}
* [Gastro Acid]{move:gastro-acid}
* [Ingrain]{move:ingrain}
* being sapped by [Leech Seed]{move:leech-seed}
* being targeted by [Lock-On]{move:lock-on} or [Mind Reader]{move:mind-reader}
* [Magnet Rise]{move:magnet-rise}
* [Perish Song]{move:perish-song}'s counter
* [Power Trick]{move:power-trick}
* [Substitute]{move:substitute}; the doll's HP is unchanged

The replacement Pokémon does not trigger effects that respond to Pokémon switching in.

Inflicts [regular damage]{mechanic:regular damage}.  Power and type are determined by the user's [IV]{mechanic:iv}s.

Power is given by `x * 40 / 63 + 30`.  `x` is obtained by arranging bit 1 from the [IV]{mechanic:iv} for each of [Special Defense]{mechanic:special defense}, [Special Attack]{mechanic:special attack}, [Speed]{mechanic:speed}, [Defense]{mechanic:defense}, [Attack]{mechanic:attack}, and [HP]{mechanic:hp} in that order.  (Bit 1 is 1 if the [IV]{mechanic:iv} is of the form `4n + 2` or `4n + 3`.  `x` is then 64 * [Special Defense]{mechanic:special defense} [IV]{mechanic:iv} bit 1, plus 32 * [Special Attack]{mechanic:special attack} [IV]{mechanic:iv} bit 1, etc.)

Power is always between 30 and 70, inclusive.  Average power is 49.5.

Type is given by `y * 15 / 63`, where `y` is similar to `x` above, except constructed from bit 0.  (Bit 0 is 1 if the [IV]{mechanic:iv} is odd.)  The result is looked up in the following table.

Value | Type
----: | --------
    0 | [Fighting]{type:fighting}
    1 | [Flying]{type:flying}
    2 | [Poison]{type:poison}
    3 | [Ground]{type:ground}
    4 | [Rock]{type:rock}
    5 | [Bug]{type:bug}
    6 | [Ghost]{type:ghost}
    7 | [Steel]{type:steel}
    8 | [Fire]{type:fire}
    9 | [Water]{type:water}
   10 | [Grass]{type:grass}
   11 | [Electric]{type:electric}
   12 | [Psychic]{type:psychic}
   13 | [Ice]{type:ice}
   14 | [Dragon]{type:dragon}
   15 | [Dark]{type:dark}

This move thus cannot be [Normal]{type:normal}.  Most other types have an equal 1/16 chance to be selected, given random [IV]{mechanic:iv}s.  However, due to the flooring used here, [Bug]{type:bug}, [Fighting]{type:fighting}, and [Grass]{type:grass} appear 5/64 of the time, and [Dark]{type:dark} only 1/64 of the time.

